Text: Getting in was a breeze...
They're likely spread thin guarding the transport.

Leaf One, along with Leaf Two and Leaf Three,
is in the middle of conducting a raid on
Mitsugoshi's headquarters.

His job is to gather up confidential documents.
Meanwhile, Leaf Two and his men will be engaging
in sabotage, while Leaf Three will be pillaging as
well as kidnapping important personnel.

Our target is the company president, an elf woman
named Luna. Let's find their office...
*gasp*

As Leaf One heads deeper into the company's bowels,
he notices a figure emerging from the darkness. He
stops in his tracks.
You...!

In the back of the store stands a beautiful
indigo-haired elf.

Welcome to Mitsugoshi. I'm Luna, the president.
I'd like to extend a warm welcome to you all.
Huh?!

The next moment, the employees standing next to
the elf named Luna suddenly move.
What the...?!
Gaaaaaah!!!
Leaf One and Leaf Two are blown away.
*gasp* But wait!

I'm not picking up on any other bodyguards around!
Her confident stance must be a bluff!
I am Leaf One—mightiest of the Clovers!

None who have stood up to me have ever lived to tell
the tale!
If you value your life, best take a little nap now!

Leaf One moves swiftly. After silently coming up
behind the target, he levels a knife-hand strike at
her neck.
Owww!
You... Wh-Wha?!

She whirls around. Although she's complaining about
the pain, she doesn’t seem to have suffered any
meaningful damage.

Come on! At least confront me head-on and let things
play out as they will!
...Uhh?
Talk about a back-stabbing customer!
With that declaration, Gamma draws her ebony blade.
Huh...?! That...black artifact... It can't be!
Heh!

I see you went to great lengths to get here, so
I would be remiss not to offer you a welcome
befitting your efforts.

My name is Gamma. And I'll be the one to end
your life!

Then she reinforces her body and closes the distance
between them in a flash.
What the—?!
She's fast! But!
Swish, swish, swish!
She's...a complete amateur!
Swish!

Hehehe... Given that footwork of yours, I take it
you're a practitioner of the Western Liechtenroi
style of fencing?
*gasp* How did you gauge that so quickly...?!

Being able to identify someone's fighting style in
just a glance requires incredible powers of
observation. Clearly, this woman is no amateur.

Either that, or she just got lucky. Leaf One isn't
sure.

Now that I know your style, countering it is easy.
Swish, swish! Swish!
She's insanely fast, but...
Heh! She said she figured out my style...

...but her attack hasn't changed a bit! She is an
amateur, after all!
Haaah!!!
Leaf One's reflexes take over. He strikes a blow.
However...
Owwwie!

Leaf One quickly falls back. She hasn't suffered so
much as a scratch.
Aaahh!

I landed a blow, I'm sure of it! Why...?
What's going on?!

For you to have landed an attack on me, you must
truly be a master. Very well.
Then I shall use my full strength against you! Swish!

Damn it! What's with that insane amount of magic?!
And what's with that absurd shout?!

She uses way too much strength, and she has wasted
movements all over the place. It doesn't matter how
fast it is, any attack with such exaggerated and
predictable movements can be easily countered.

However, Gamma's sword has enough magic packed into
it to blow away dozens of dark knights with ease.

One touch of that thing would be lethal. Leaf One
evades Gamma's assault in one exaggerated motion.
It's a trick my magnificent master taught me!
Let's see. Gamma...
Your numbers are off the chart.
So, how about...

He told me to infuse my sword with a bunch of magic,
then slash!
Gamma's immense magic power causes a wall to crumble.
Agh...!

He also told me that if I shout while I'm
attacking, it'll look more powerful!
Fwoosh, fwoosh—
Their thoughts align.
She got him! It's over!
However, reality doesn't align.
Agh!
Gamma yelps as she trips and falls over nothing.
A tremendous bang echoes throughout the corridor.
Huh...?
Hehe... Not bad.

Faking a retreat only to set up ingenious terrain
traps!
What a classic Liechtenroi swordmaster!
Your nose is bleeding.
Leaf One shudders upon seeing Gamma rise unharmed.

A-Anyway, I don't want to interact with this woman...
I mean, it appears she's too much for me to handle...

Quit messing around, you two! Let's fall back for
now—

Leaf Two and Leaf Three will finish up their tasks
soon. As the thought crosses Leaf One's mind, he
hears footsteps behind him.
If you're looking for your lost friends...
Wha—?!
They've been well looked after.

Without a doubt, they're the bodies of his fellow
Clovers.

When he glances at the woman, she doesn't look like
anything more than a simple Mitsugoshi employee.
Be careful, both of you...!
Ack!

That man has mastered the Liechtenroi style of
fencing... He's undoubtedly one of the world's
greatest masters.
Really. How impressive.

The other employee looks at Leaf One. Ninety percent
of what fills her gaze is doubt.
N-No, I'm not—

But I've seen through all your abilities. From here
on out, I won't hold back!
Give me a break...!

Leaf One senses some kind of unknown power within
Mitsugoshi.
Damn it!
You're not going anywhere!

However, Leaf One can read her like a book. He had
grasped Gamma's attack range and knew he could
escape.
At least, that was the plan.
Aah!
If only she hadn't tripped.
Whoa!

Unfortunately for him, Gamma stumbling causes her to
lose her grip on her sword.
It goes spinning toward Leaf One and...
...unleashes a burst of magic.
Hehehe...
Behold, my Hidden Technique...
...Suicide Swing!
Your nose is bleeding.
